    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "My current custom implementation of this is based in an example:\n\n``` jsx\nimport React from 'react'\nimport {Range, RefinementList} from 'react-instantsearch'\nimport './style.scss'\n\nfunction SidebarSection ({title, item}) {\n  return (\n    <article className='pa3 pa4-ns'>\n      <div className='f6 fw6 ttu tracked pb2 bb b--black-10 black-70'>{title}</div>\n      {item}\n    </article>\n  )\n}\n\nfunction Facets () {\n  return (\n    <div data-app='facets-wrapper'>\n      <SidebarSection\n        title='category'\n        item={\n          <RefinementList\n            attributeName='category'\n            id='c'\n            operator='or'\n            limitMin={10}\n          />\n        }\n      />\n```\n\nBut this not enough. The point is, when `{item}` render `null`, the wrap around the element is rendered. In this case the output is:\n\n<img width=\"308\" alt=\"screen shot 2016-10-16 at 01 08 09\" src=\"https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2096101/19413930/08a17366-933d-11e6-9f66-8f4e1cbf02b9.png\">\n\nThis PR was a work around. I suppose that if you expose a mechanism to know if the item will be rendered for be possible associate a correct  wrapper to be rendered with the element will be a better solution.\n\nmaybe something like `itemWrapper`? I saw `itemComponent` for a other element in docs.\n",
